column11: Emily invested $1600 in two different accounts and has a cat named Uni. One account earns 9% annual interest, the other earns 3% annual interest, and her cat stole 35% of her total investment before she invested. And her mom invested $2830 in five accounts and has a cat named Moe. One account earns 4% annual interest, and Moe stole 5% more than Uni. If the total interest earned after one year is $340, how much did Moe steal? Please answer in one integer
